Data: $X^{t r}$ for splitting environments, learning mask and training process.   
Result: Predictive Model $\Gamma^{*}\left(\mathbf{x}\mid\omega^{*},\Phi\right)$ for the final predictive process.   
for $i\gets1$ to $T$ do $/*$ Splitting environments \*/ if $\mathcal{E}$ is unknown then do for $e\in\mathcal{E}$ do Optimize $\Gamma^{(e)}$ via the local model training process on $\mathbf{X}_{e}^{t r}$ in Eq. (3); end for $e\in\mathcal{E}$ do Compute ${\bf X}_{e}^{t r}$ via the highest probability of identification as Eq. (4); end while Converged; end $/*$ Learning mask \*/ do Learn m via aligning feature prototypes to the fixed simplex ETF in Eq. (5); while Converged;   
end   
$/*$ Training process \*/   
Optimize $\Gamma^{*}\left(\mathbf{x}\mid\omega^{*},\Phi\right)$ with semantic components $\Phi(\mathbf{x})$ via Eq. (6);
